      "content": "High-pitched squealing after a brake job can be caused by several things, but start by inspecting your new brake pads. Sometimes, the pads aren't seated correctly, or you might need to thoroughly bed them in according to your car's manual. If the new pads seem fine, check the brake rotor surfaces for any unevenness or dust build-up.",
