    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk i checked the pads and they look seated right. the squeal is really piercing though, almost like a metal-on-metal screeching sound. could it be the caliper pins are seized or something? i'm worried i missed something during the install.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A piercing, metal-on-metal screech suggests the brake components are not making solid contact, so inspecting the caliper pins for any signs of corrosion or sticking is a good next step. Ensure the caliper slide pins move freely when you manually push them; if they are seized, the caliper won't clamp evenly. If you suspect a missed connection or improper torque while installing, double-checking your wheel lug nuts, caliper bolts, and bracket mounting bolts is also wise.",
      "source": "target",
