      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sudden, deep screech can indicate something loose or out of alignment rather than a gradual component wear. Thoroughly check all hardware, including any metal clips, retaining clips, or guide pin hardware that might have been disturbed during the pad replacement. While random issues happen, consistent severe noise usually points back to improper assembly or component binding within the caliper assembly.",
